cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.HC, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on evaluating the cost-effectiveness of automated GUI testing for a real-world software system. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also likely as the paper discusses the maintenance cost and ROI of GUI automation scripts as a system evolves. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper compares two fundamentally different AGT tools, namely Selenium and EyeAutomate, in terms of their implementation time and maintenance cost. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper also reports on the usability of the two AGT tools. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of AGT on manual testing activities and the potential benefits of increasing test frequency.
